README for ALPS applications developers

* How to make a snapshot?

1) Just type `make snapshot' at the top directory, which generates
   alps-applications-YYYYMMDD.tar.gz, where YYYY = year, MM = month,
   and DD = day.


* How to update preamble of files?

1) Edit preamble.in.  Note that keywords @COPYRIGHT@ and @ID@ will be
   replaced by appropriate strings.

2) Type make update-preamble at the top directory.


* [Checklist] How to release a new version and prepare the
  distribution file?

1) Check version: Edit line 15 in configure.ac.

2) Regenerate configure script by typing

     ./bootstrap

   at the top-level source directory.

3) Check all the documentations and ChangeLog.

4) ./configure && make update-preamble

5) make

6) svn commit

7) make snapshot

   Check alps-applications-*.tar.gz

   [[[Go to step 1, if you have a problem.]]]

8) make a tag for release

   ex) svn copy https://alps.comp-phys.org/svn/alps1/trunk/applications https://alps.comp-phys.org/svn/alps1/tags/applications-1.3

9) ./configure && make release

   alps-applications-X.X.tar.gz, where X.X = verison number

10) Copy the tar ball to the web server and update web page.
